<br>
First off i do feel that warriors do need help. Somethign really needs to be done soon because its only going to get worse in PoP.<br>
<br>
Sorry i dont have time to read this whole thread, but here is what i think needs to be done.<br>
<br>
1) Mitigation is ass broken. Somethign is really wrong when a tank class values their avoidance skils 10 times over their mitigation skills. And thats the way it currently is, i dont give an ass about my mitigation ac but ill take all the avoidance i can get. AC hasent really ment anythign since kunark, and that really needs to be changed. The whole mitigation system really needs a rewrite. Warriors need to be either on a much higher mitigation table or need some kinda built in defensive skill making them take less then max hit 100% of the time. In addition to that i feel knights also should be on a higher table and/or have a build in type of defensive, BUT we should definately be lower then warrios. In short tho the tank classes need to be set apart from all the rest in the area of mitigation, right now were all the same.<br>
<br>
2) Shields dont do and never have done anything. When tanking people really should be using shields, be it a knight or a warrior. Right now youd have to be a moron to do so. Main reason being shields dont do anything they only add stats. Second reason being you lose a huge amout of DPS when you equip a shield, lower dps means you cant maintain agro as easy. Sheilds really need a purpose in the game. If they gave you a 20% chance to outright block a skill youd see people using them, if they gave a 20% defensive youd see people using them. But, they also need to do somethign about the reduced ability to control agro when a shield is equipped or fixing shields still has that glaring flaw. In short a 1h weapon + shield shoudl be a viable form of combat. Rigth now it is not to any class.<br>
<br>
3) +Hitpoints on items. +hitpoints should have scaled based on classes. +100=100 for a warrior and much less for other classes. But, this late in the game i dont know if they coudl get away with fixing this correctly, and thus they will probably leave it alone. If they however fix mitigation properly it will help the situation a lot. From day 1 hitpoints really should ahve scaled tho. This would have allowed the tank classes especially warriors maintain their hp leads over other classes.<br>
<br>
4) agro management. I dont know if you can just outright give warriors a much better taunt without breaking the game badly. I do agree somethign needs to be done in this area however. A warrior shoudl nto have to rely on proccing +hate weapons as much as they do. However they should also not have the ability to control agro as well as a paladin/shadowknight should. Warriors should be the better tank, but we shoudl be the better agro lockers. I dont know how they can corretly fix this without trivilizing the game. If you have a warrior that can maintain perfect agro then thigns are way too easy; but it is a joke right now and needs work.<br>
<br>
<br>
Now for the people who like to bitch about the paladin class in this thread, a large /ruide. Dont even try to give the old well they get this skill and that skill blah blah blah and we dont. Or the old my skills suck but yours are godly. If you are gonna post any comparison of skills do it with the facts not some bloated comparsion of blatent exaggerations. For the first time in 3 years my class has not been severly handicapped. We are not godly, but we also do not have anymore glareing holes. We still have a few issues, but that will always be true for any class.<br>
<br>
In short to verant, fix mitigation damnit! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ucslochraven.showPublicProfile?language=EN>CSLochraven</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 180<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/8/02 8:08:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=907.topic&index=418>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://gs.cdnow.com/graphics/COVERART/local/L/80/01/00138001.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_ale.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: rofl</span><hr size=1> I like the idea about shields.<br>
