<br>
From seventhsword:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> End result is the warrior class is working as intended and needs no upgrades to stay balanced. It should only receive upgrades if pal/sk/monks/ect receive upgrades of their own to keep the current balance.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Its simple why warriors need to be re-balanced:<br>
<br>
We were balanced in with the all other melee classes in SoV era based upon our superior armor and how much melee power and class abilities we had vs the lesser armors, different melee powers and class powers they had.<br>
<br>
Now we no longer have the best gear, instead the same gear is shared by most if not all of the other classes. Warriors lost nothing directly here, however the other classes became as powerful as a warrior in this point.<br>
<br>
The hybrid classes, sans bards, have received the full force of the caster balance without suffering any drawbacks to the melee side of their powers. The healing hybrid classes have also received part of the priest balance as to date. <br>
<br>
So yes the other classes did receive more. Now it is time to give warriors something to restore the balance, the only question left is what.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uchavr.showPublicProfile?language=EN>chavr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/8/02 11:13:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=907.topic&index=421>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_rip.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: rip</span><hr size=1> Warriors set the standard.  They are 100.  Balancing started to happen.  The hybrids were at 40 or so.  Now hybrids are at 100.  Warriors see this as them losing power.  All that really happened was the huge gap between them closed.<br>
<br>
When adjusting anything to do with mitigation include the knight classes along with the warrior class.  We are the only tanks in the game.<br>
<br>
Someone posted that warriors only bring tanking because their offense was well below the other melee.  Thank you for proving my point about paladins.  We have even less offense then warriors.  <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Personally, I prefer to not be the main tank in a group.  It's not what I enjoy doing.  Sadly there are only two ways I get in a group though.  The first is because of friends/people I've grouped with before.  People know me and know I'm a damn good paladin.  This is probably the majority of my groups now a days.  The second way is when a group is looking for a tank.  Usually in these groups I tank as long as it takes to get a warrior in the group and then let them take over.  At that point I do what I enjoy doing most.  All sorts of different things.<br>
<br>
Before the upgrades luclin brought to us I didn't get groups that needed a tank though.  The only time I got in a non guild group was when there was no one else left lfg in the zone.  I had to be in guild groups and then would meet new people that filled in the holes that developed.  Once these people got to know me and how I played I could get in groups with them again.  It was a very long and drawn out process to make connections in such a way to get a group.<br>
<br>
I fear that if the tank label is once again removed from paladins things will go back to the way they were.  If you ask for adjustments to warriors make sure knights are not left out when it comes to tanking.  <br>
<br>
I can't convey to you the way it used to feel to play a paladin.  I can not get you to understand the frustration one felt some days.  The only reason I got groups remotely easily is because I could eek out every last trick from my class.  There was no other option for me if I hoped for people to invite me again.  Finally though I don't have to be frustrated anymore.  My class has finally come into it's own, and it's only a matter of showing people that paladins are no longer the black sheep we once were.  <br>
<br>
Then I find out about this thread and start reading.  I see warriors saying that paladins are getting groups all the time.  I see warriors complaining because paladins are being picked now for one of the 6 spots in a group.  Warriors are saying they've been left behind.  They are no longer useful.  Warriors should be the only viable option for a tank.  No one else should be able to encroach upon this holiest of holy spots.  Yet, they totally neglect the fact there are 3 plate/tank classes.  They ignore the fact that we are tanks too.  That if warriors are made into the best options for tanks, groups will no longer want us knights.  You say we have utility and that tanking isn't our only option.  You forget that there is almost never a group looking for a utility class.  <br>
<br>
<br>
Do warriors need looking into? Maybe, I honestly couldn't make that opinon.  I am an expert on paladins.  That is who I am and what I know.  When I tell you that placing warriors definitevly above paladins in tanking, again, will hurt us severely, then trust that I am right.  Find a solution to your problem that will not hurt my class along the way.  <br>
<br>
Finaly, remember this.  Even with all the balancing and things done for paladins there is one true statement.  Warriors are still better tanks.  The difference is Paladins now bring enough other things to the table to offset their weaker tanking ability.  Finally we have become even in desirabilty to groups, and now you want to elevate yourselves again. <br>
